'''Corsair battleships''', sometimes known simply as '''corsairs''', were ships that served in the [[Navy/Legends|navy]] of the [[Brotherhood of Darkness/Legends|Brotherhood of Darkness]] during the final stages of the [[New Sith Wars]].

==Characteristics==
Although in other contexts the term [[Battleship/Legends|battleship]] denoted large, heavily armored combatants, corsair battleships were relatively fast-moving and maneuverable ships. In this period, it seems that the "battleship" designation described attack/picket ships, which served along with [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] in a support role for larger [[Warship/Legends|warships]], such as [[Sith Destroyer]]s and [[Dreadnaught cruiser|Dreadnaughts]], or the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Hammerhead-class cruiser|''Hammerhead''-class cruisers]].

==History==
Two ships of this class were [[Rage (corsair battleship)|''Rage'']] and [[Fury (corsair battleship)|''Fury'']], both of which formed part of the Sith fleet that fought in the [[First Battle of Ruusan]] in [[1002 BBY]].

